column1: This dataset comprises surface water quality, water temperature profiles, and meteorological data  recorded at the Lough Feeagh Automatic Water Quality Monitoring Station (AWQMS) from 2004 to current.
The AWQMS records data at high freqency and records on a Campbell scientific data logger.
The AWQMS is permanently moored in 45 metres of water located at 53.946 N, -9.577 W
Almost all of the data are at a 2 min time step, apart from the period 2008-03-27 16:10:00 until 2009-02-03 00:30:00, when data were recorded every 5 minutes.
DateTime is in GMT (Greemwich  and are not corrected for summer time.
Maintenance logs can be found in the "Comments" file

column12: custom made chain with sensors giving a basic accuracy of the sensor of ±0.03°C.  The accuracy of the overall system will not be quite as good as this (because of other factors such as the measuring accuracy of the logger), but should be better than ±0.1°C

Some years, these data were recorded in knots, and in other years, m/sec. A quick check is that the average wind speed over any time period should give ~5 m/sec or ~10 knots. A compiled /QA/Qced wind speed is available on request through data.marine.ie
